\",\n670:           \"ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\"\n671:         ],\n672:         \"requiredBehaviors\": [\n673:           \"`Profile.kt` only renders the packaged profile avatar with static user text; it does not open an image viewer, decode bitmaps, inspect EXIF metadata, or support zoom/preview gestures.\",\n674:           \"`Profile.kt` renders a back command, static profile action cards, and a logout button. The back arrow calls `navController.navigateUp()`, the action cards keep placeholder click handlers, and logout clears the start destination stack before routing to onboa...\",\n675:           \"`Profile.kt` composes against `ProfileViewModel` callbacks and navigates immediately from user actions, while keeping the visible profile identity and placeholder cards static until logout is requested.\",\n676:           \"`Profile.kt` uses only packaged resources, local click handlers, and navigation callbacks; it does not request runtime permissions or access protected Android APIs.\",\n677:           \"`ProfileViewModel.onEvent` propagates the logout action by toggling login state and then invoking the navigation callback, so the profile screen reacts immediately to the logout event.\",\n678:           \"`ProfileViewModel.onEvent` only toggles persisted login state and invokes the logout callback; it does not request permissions or call protected APIs.\",\n679:           \"`ProfileViewModel` has no independent load/resume teardown path; its lifecycle responsibility is limited to servicing the logout event while the profile screen is active.\",\n680:           \"`ProfileEvent.kt` defines only the `PerformLogout` callback payload and does not represent permission requests, results, or protected API access.\"\n681:         ],\n682:         \"riskHints\": [\n683:           \"critical/high behavior cannot close on build pass alone\"\n684:         ],\n685:         \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n686:           \"Closed critical/high features must record sourc